api-reference_46.content:
The main database class for vector storage and retrieval operations.

```typescript
import { VectorDB } from 'ruvector';

class VectorDB {
  /**
   * Create a new VectorDB instance
   * @param options - Database configuration options
   */
  constructor(options?: DbOptions);

  /**
   * Initialize the database connection
   * @returns Promise resolving when initialization is complete
   */
  async initialize(): Promise<void>;

  /**
   * Create a new collection
   * @param name - Collection name (must be unique)
   * @param config - Collection configuration
   * @returns Promise resolving to the created collection
   */
  async createCollection(name: string, config: CollectionConfig): Promise<Collection>;

  /**
   * Get an existing collection by name
   * @param name - Collection name
   * @returns Promise resolving to the collection or null if not found
   */
  async getCollection(name: string): Promise<Collection | null>;

  /**
   * Delete a collection
   * @param name - Collection name to delete
   * @returns Promise resolving to boolean indicating success
   */
  async deleteCollection(name: string): Promise<boolean>;

  /**
   * List all collections in the database
   * @returns Promise resolving to array of collection names
   */
  async listCollections(): Promise<string[]>;

  /**
   * Get database health status
   * @returns Promise resolving to health response
   */
  async health(): Promise<HealthResponse>;

  /**
   * Close database connection and cleanup resources
   */
  async close(): Promise<void>;
}
```

**Example Usage:**

```typescript
import { VectorDB, DistanceMetric } from 'ruvector';

const db = new VectorDB({
  path: './data/vectors.db',
  cacheSize: 1024 * 1024 * 100, // 100MB cache
});

await db.initialize();

const collection = await db.createCollection('embeddings', {
  dimension: 1536,
  distanceMetric: DistanceMetric.Cosine,
  hnsw: {
    m: 16,
    efConstruction: 200,
    efSearch: 100,
  },
});
```

