api-reference_328.content:
Configuration for Hierarchical Navigable Small World (HNSW) index.

```typescript
interface HnswConfig {
  /**
   * Number of bi-directional links per node
   * Higher = better recall, more memory
   * @default 16
   * @range 4-64
   */
  m: number;

  /**
   * Size of dynamic candidate list during construction
   * Higher = better index quality, slower build
   * @default 200
   * @range 100-500
   */
  efConstruction: number;

  /**
   * Size of dynamic candidate list during search
   * Higher = better recall, slower search
   * @default 100
   * @range 10-500
   */
  efSearch: number;

  /**
   * Maximum number of layers in the graph
   * @default auto-calculated based on dataset size
   */
  maxLayers?: number;

  /**
   * Enable multi-threading during construction
   * @default true
   */
  parallelConstruction?: boolean;

  /**
   * Number of threads for parallel operations
   * @default number of CPU cores
   */
  numThreads?: number;
}
```

**Example Usage:**

```typescript
// High-recall configuration for production
const productionHnsw: HnswConfig = {
  m: 32,
  efConstruction: 400,
  efSearch: 200,
  parallelConstruction: true,
  numThreads: 8,
};

// Fast configuration for development
const devHnsw: HnswConfig = {
  m: 8,
  efConstruction: 100,
  efSearch: 50,
};
```

