api-reference_400.content:
Configuration for vector quantization to reduce memory usage.

```typescript
interface QuantizationConfig {
  /**
   * Quantization type
   * - 'none': No quantization (full precision)
   * - 'scalar': Scalar quantization (8-bit)
   * - 'product': Product quantization (compressed)
   * - 'binary': Binary quantization (1-bit)
   */
  type: 'none' | 'scalar' | 'product' | 'binary';

  /**
   * Number of subquantizers for product quantization
   * Must divide vector dimension evenly
   * @default 8
   */
  numSubquantizers?: number;

  /**
   * Number of centroids per subquantizer
   * @default 256
   */
  numCentroids?: number;

  /**
   * Training sample size for quantization codebook
   * @default 10000
   */
  trainingSamples?: number;

  /**
   * Enable rescoring with original vectors
   * Improves accuracy at cost of speed
   * @default true
   */
  rescore?: boolean;
}
```

**Example Usage:**

```typescript
// Memory-efficient configuration (4x compression)
const compressedConfig: QuantizationConfig = {
  type: 'scalar',
  rescore: true,
};

// Maximum compression (32x compression)
const maxCompressionConfig: QuantizationConfig = {
  type: 'product',
  numSubquantizers: 16,
  numCentroids: 256,
  trainingSamples: 50000,
  rescore: true,
};
```

