api-reference_3012.content:
Signatures define the input/output contract for modules.

```typescript
/**
 * Signature definition for module input/output
 */
interface Signature {
  /**
   * Signature name
   */
  name?: string;

  /**
   * Natural language description
   */
  description?: string;

  /**
   * Input field definitions
   */
  inputs: FieldDefinition[];

  /**
   * Output field definitions
   */
  outputs: FieldDefinition[];
}

/**
 * Field definition for signature inputs/outputs
 */
interface FieldDefinition {
  /**
   * Field name (used as key in input/output objects)
   */
  name: string;

  /**
   * Field description for LLM
   */
  description?: string;

  /**
   * Field type hint
   */
  type?: 'string' | 'number' | 'boolean' | 'array' | 'object';

  /**
   * Whether field is required
   * @default true
   */
  required?: boolean;

  /**
   * Default value if not provided
   */
  default?: unknown;

  /**
   * Prefix for output formatting
   */
  prefix?: string;
}
```

**Signature String Syntax:**

```typescript
// Simple signature: "input_field -> output_field"
const qa = "question -> answer";

// Multiple inputs: "input1, input2 -> output"
const summarize = "document, max_length -> summary";

// Multiple outputs: "input -> output1, output2"
const analyze = "text -> sentiment, confidence";

// With descriptions: "input: description -> output: description"
const classify = "text: The text to classify -> category: One of [positive, negative, neutral]";
```

